Step-by-Step Solution
1Ô∏è‚É£ Add a ‚ÄúPrint‚Äù Button Next to Close Button

In your _ArchVehiclePopUp.cshtml, update this part:

<div class="popup-close">
    <button type="button" class="k-button k-button-icon" onclick="closeArchVehiclePopup()">
        <span class="k-icon k-i-close"></span>
    </button>
</div>


‚û° Replace it with:

<div class="popup-header-buttons">
    <button type="button" class="k-button k-button-icon" onclick="printArchVehiclePopup()">
        <span class="k-icon k-i-print"></span> Print
    </button>
    <button type="button" class="k-button k-button-icon" onclick="closeArchVehiclePopup()">
        <span class="k-icon k-i-close"></span> Close
    </button>
</div>

2Ô∏è‚É£ Add the Print Script in @section scripts

At the bottom of the same file, inside @section scripts, add:

@section scripts {
    <script>
        function closeArchVehiclePopup() {
            var wnd = $(".k-window-content:visible").data("kendoWindow");
            if (wnd) wnd.close();
        }

        function printArchVehiclePopup() {
            // Get the popup content (just the inner HTML)
            var popupContent = document.querySelector(".archvehicle-popup-style").innerHTML;

            // Create a new window for printing
            var printWindow = window.open('', '', 'width=950,height=700');

            // Copy styles from the main page (includes Kendo CSS)
            var styles = '';
            document.querySelectorAll('link[rel="stylesheet"], style').forEach(link => {
                styles += link.outerHTML;
            });

            // Write content to the print window
            printWindow.document.write(`
                <html>
                    <head>
                        <title>Archive Vehicle Details</title>
                        ${styles}
                        <style>
                            body {
                                font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
                                margin: 20px;
                            }
                            .archvehicle-popup-style {
                                width: 100%;
                                height: auto;
                                overflow: visible;
                            }
                            .popup-header-buttons {
                                display: none !important; /* hide print/close buttons on print */
                            }
                            .k-grid {
                                page-break-inside: avoid;
                            }
                        </style>
                    </head>
                    <body>
                        <div class="archvehicle-popup-style">
                            ${popupContent}
                        </div>
                        <script>
                            window.onload = function() {
                                window.focus();
                                window.print();
                                window.close();
                            };
                        <\/script>
                    </body>
                </html>
            `);
            printWindow.document.close();
        }
    </script>
}

3Ô∏è‚É£ Optional CSS Enhancement

To keep things neat, replace .popup-close with .popup-header-buttons in your CSS section:

.popup-header-buttons {
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
}

